subjective.chief_complaint: Generally unwell, sore throat, runny nose
subjective.hpi: Patient presents with a 4-7 day history of feeling generally unwell, with a sore throat, runny nose, fatigue, myalgia, and joint pain. Symptoms include a sore throat and dry, constant cough. They report nasal congestion and night sweats over 4-7 days, with an initial fever that settled with paracetamol/ibuprofen. No chest pain. Shortness of breath noted on exertion. Reports generalized, intermittent headaches with no visual symptoms or photophobia. Denies nausea, vomiting, bowel or urinary symptoms. Drinking fluids but has reduced appetite. No rashes.
subjective.patient_history: No significant past medical history (PMH nil). No known drug history (DH nil). NKDA. Family history of Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus (T2DM) in grandmother. Lives alone, works as an accountant, is an occasional smoker and occasional alcohol (etOH) consumer. Reports stressful work but no mood symptoms.

primary_diagnosis.value: Viral Upper Respiratory Tract Infection / Influenza
